news.title: Gujarat: 30-35% increase in sale deed registrations since Navratri
news.para: The officer has also ordered each sub-registrar office to issue 61 appointment tokens daily. There are 43 sub-registrar offices in the state that register property sale deeds, and 12 of these offices are in Ahmedabad.

news.title: Punjab CM approves hike in minimum wages of construction workers
news.para: The CM said minimum wages of unskilled workers have been hiked to Rs 9,907 from existing Rs 9,192 whereas that of semi-skilled have been enhanced to Rs 10,687 from Rs 9,972.

news.title: Tamil Nadu seeks time to submit report on registration of plots
news.para: The petitioner alleged that two people were selling residential plots in Veerapandi village in the district without obtaining layout approval from the executive officer of Veerapandi town panchayat.

news.title: Chandigarh estate office recovers Rs 85 crore dues since April 2022
news.para: The dues pertain to unpaid rent on leasehold properties, penalties on misuse of properties and building violations. Some of these dues were pending for last more than a decade.

news.title: Delhi LG launches portal for digital management of DDA's land records
news.para: ​The portal 'Land Management Information System' (LMIS) is also aimed at effective and efficient management and protection of DDA land records, said an official statement.

news.title: Raze illegal walls & farmhouses built in Faridabad Aravalis in 15 days, owners told
news.para: A total of 600 structures have been identified in Ankhir and Mewla Maharajpur villages, whereas ground truthing (an exercise to verify data collected through aerial photography or satellite radar via ground visits) of illegal structures is still going on in Anangpur and Lakkarpur villages.

news.title: In two decades, 2,253 maps approved in Ghaziabad but only 221 CCs given out
news.para: Data shared by the GDA showed that it had approved 2,253 building layouts in the past 18 years. But only 221 of these projects have CCs till date.

news.title: Adani Group in talks to buy Jaiprakash's cement units for Rs 5,000 crore
news.para: Jaypee group had sold its cement business to UltraTech but a few units were still housed in group firms. The boards of Jaiprakash Associates Ltd and Jaiprakash Power Ventures Ltd on Monday approved plans to divest their cement business as well as some non-core assets to reduce debt.

news.title: India Cements divests entire stake in SMPL to JSW Cement for Rs 477 crore
news.para: The company has "entered into a Share Purchase Agreement on October 10, 2022, with JSW Cement Limited (Buyer) and divested the entire shareholdings held by it in SMPL, for a total consideration of Rs 476.87 crore," India Cements Ltd (ICL) said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: NRJN Family Trust buys residential property worth Rs 59 crore in Bengaluru
news.para: The property measuring 9,600 sq. ft. with a total built up area of 4,200 sq. ft is situated at 3rd Block, Koramangala Extension, Bengaluru.

news.title: Bidhannagar civic body to come up with rehabilitation plan to shift Bagjola encroachers
news.para: The condition of the canal has deteriorated over the years due to unauthorised encroachment on its side. The irrigation department is dredging the entire Bagjola canal and the work is expected to be completed by December this year.

news.title: Co-living startup Settl to add 1,000 beds in Hyderabad
news.para: "With return to office picking up, the demand for managed rented accommodation has significantly increased. All our centres in Hyderabad is doing very well. We will be adding 1000 more beds by end of FY'2023," Settl Co-Founder Abhishek Tripathi said in a statement.

news.title: Jaiprakash Associates & Jaiprakash Power Ventures to divest their cement businesses
news.para: The companies' decision to sell their cement business also comes against the backdrop of a recent plea by the country's biggest lender SBI to initiate insolvency proceedings against Jaypee group's flagship firm Jaiprakash Associates Ltd (JAL).

news.title: Bank of Maharashtra raises lending rate by 20 bps
news.para: The benchmark one-year MCLR will be 7.80 per cent from Monday, as against 7.60 per cent. The one-year rate is used to fix most consumer loans such as auto, personal and home loans.

news.title: Nagpur improvement trust 'defies' norms to allow commercial use of Gorepeth
news.para: Around 40 residents from Gorepeth, including former advocate general of Chhattisgarh high court Jugalkishore Gilda, submitted a complaint to the NIT chairman Manoj Kumar Suryawanshi and municipal commissioner Radhakrishnan B demanding action against violators and concerned officials.
